EXPLANATION
BY THE LEGISLATIVE COUNCIL
OF
A N A C T
RELATING TO COURTS AND CIVIL PROCEDURE -- COURTS -- JUDICIAL SELECTION
***
1 This act would set a mandatory retirement age of seventy-five (75) for all justices and
2 magistrates of the superior, district, workers’ compensation, family and traffic tribunal courts who
3 are initially appointed after July 1, 2025 and provide that no pension or retirement benefits be
4 affected thereby.
5 This act would take effect on July 1, 2025.
